  "slug": "cauliflower-cream-soup",
  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Preheat oven to 200C. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables. **Cauliflower:** separate florets from the root, remove green leaves from the root and discard the leaves, halve the root. **Garlic:** peel. **Onion:** dice. **Parsley:** finely chop.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Distribute the cauliflower and garlic on the baking sheet. Grease using olive oil, and season with salt, black pepper, and a sprinkle of dried jalapeños.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Roast for about 15 minutes, toss and roast for another 15 minutes until the cauliflower is soft and charred a bit. Remove from the oven, and cool down.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the cauliflower is cooling, put a large pot over medium-high heat with a bit of olive oil.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the onion to the pot. Cook, frequently stirring, until softened but not browned, about 4 minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the chicken stock to the pot.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the lime zest, <Ingredient name=\"cinnamon\"  />, <Ingredient name=\"curry powder\"  />, and chili flakes to the pot, and stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Transfer cauliflower (except the smallest florets) and garlic to the pot. Add enough water to barely cover the cauliflower and bring to a simmer.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Purée the soup using a blender until completely smooth. Add lime juice and more stock or water to achieve desired consistency.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Season with salt and pepper.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Serve topped with the rest of the cauliflower florets, and parsley.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
